## Migration Conventions

- Use numbered files: `001_create_users.sql`, `002_add_orders.sql`
- Every migration has an `up` and a `down`
- Never ALTER COLUMN to a breaking type — add a new column, migrate data, drop old
- Never DROP without a prior migration disabling FK references

```sql
-- migrations/003_add_metrics.up.sql
CREATE TABLE metrics (
    id          UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    sensor_id   UUID        NOT NULL REFERENCES sensors(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    value       NUMERIC(10,4) NOT NULL,
    recorded_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_metrics_sensor_time
    ON metrics (sensor_id, recorded_at DESC);

-- migrations/003_add_metrics.down.sql
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS metrics;
```

